      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes. GCC doesn\u0027t \"see\" through the checks in GetPtraceScope(). At the same time it seems a bit fragile to depend on static analysis to catch mistakes here and for human readers it\u0027s even harder (the DCHECK(false) sends mixed signals: either that path can absolutely never be hit, so the DCHECK is useless, or it might get hit, then it would be possible to return a indeterminate value in release builds)\n\nDo you want me to remove this change?",
